The paper deals with the Steiner tree problem in the distributed computing model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves algorithms and optimization, which are topics covered in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Applied Computing (cs.AL). The paper also deals with network communication and message complexity, which are topics covered in the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
